        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 8:56AM CDT by NWS Grand Forks ND</headline>
        <description>At 856 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gardner, or 23 miles northwest of Fargo, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Arthur, Hendrum, Hunter, Argusville, Grandin, Georgetown, and Amenia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Grand Forks.</instruction>
